# Project Conventions

## Constants Location

All hardcoded constant content must be placed in the `constant/` folder at the project root.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Constants defined inline in components
const CATEGORIES = ["Sans Serif", "Serif", "Display"];
const NAV_ITEMS = [{ name: "Home", path: "/" }];

// ✅ GOOD - Import from constant folder
import { TYPEFACE_CATEGORIES } from "@/constant/TYPEFACE_CATEGORIES";
import { NAV_ITEMS } from "@/constant/NAV_ITEMS";
```

### Naming Convention

- Use SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for constant names
- File name should match the exported constant name
- One constant per file (or related group)

```
constant/
  TYPEFACE_CATEGORIES.ts
  NAV_ITEMS.ts
  SUPPORTED_LANGUAGES.ts
  ACCEPTED_FONT_FORMATS.ts
```

## Type Declarations

Always use `type` instead of `interface` for type declarations. All types should be in the `types/` folder.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Using interface
interface User {
  id: string;
  name: string;
}

// ✅ GOOD - Using type
type User = {
  id: string;
  name: string;
};
```

### Type Location

- Global/shared types go in `types/` folder
- Component-specific types can be defined in the same file

```
types/
  studio.ts
  typefaces.ts
  cart.ts
  index.ts  // barrel export
```
